IRS990.MissionDesc: THE CARPENTERS' JOINT TRAINING FUND OF ST. LOUIS ADMITS STUDENTS OF ANY RACE, COLOR, NATIONAL AND ETHNIC ORIGIN TO ALL OF THE RIGHTS, PRIVILEGES, PROGRAMS AND ACTIVITIES GENERALLY ACCORDED OR MADE AVAILABLE TO STUDENTS AT ITS SCHOOL. IT DOES NOT DISCRIMINATE ON THE BASIS OF RACE, COLOR, OR NATIONAL AND ETHNIC ORIGIN IN THE ADMINISTRATION OF ITS EDUCATIONAL POLICIES, ADMISSIONS POLICIES, SCHOLARSHIP AND LOAN PROGRAMS, AND ATHLETIC AND OTHER SCHOOL-ADMINISTERED PROGRAMS.
IRS990.Desc: THE TRAINING SCHOOL PROVIDES EDUCATION AND TRAINING TO THE CARPENTRY MEMBERS OF THE ST LOUIS-KANSAS CITY CARPENTERS REGIONAL COUNCIL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: IN ACCORDANCE WITH GAAP, THE PLAN'S MANAGEMENT IS REQUIRED TO EVALUATE TAX POSITIONS TAKEN BY THE FUND AND RECOGNIZE A TAX LIABILITY IF THE FUND HAS TAKEN AN UNCERTAIN POSITION THAT MORE LIKELY THAN NOT WOULD NOT BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY THE APPLICABLE TAXING AUTHORITIES. THE PLAN'S MANAGEMENT HAS ANALYZED THE TAX POSITIONS TAKEN BY THE FUND AND HAS CONCLUDED THAT AS OF APRIL 30, 2022 AND 2021, THERE ARE NO UNCERTAIN POSITIONS TAKEN, OR EXPECTED TO BE TAKEN, THAT WOULD REQUIRE RECOGNITION OF A LIABILITY OR DISCLOSURE IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE FUND IS NO LONGER SUBJECT TO INCOME TAX EXAMINATIONS FOR YEARS PRIOR TO 2019. THE FUND IS ALSO SUBJECT TO ROUTINE AUDITS BY THE DEPARTMENT OF LABOR, GENERALLY FOR SIX YEARS AFTER THE STATUTORY DUE DATE OF THE ANNUAL INFORMATION RETURN. THERE ARE CURRENTLY NO AUDITS IN PROGRESS FOR ANY TAX PERIODS.

THE SCHOOL SERVES ALL MEMBERS OF THE ST. LOUIS KANSAS-CITY CARPENTERS REGIONAL COUNCIL. THIS ORGANIZATION COMMUNICATES ITS RACIALLY NONDISCRIMINATORY POLICY THROUGH NEWSLETTERS DISTRIBUTED TO ALL MEMBERS OF THE UNION AND ON ITS WEBSITE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS PRESENTED TO THE GOVERNING BODY AND THE ORGANIZATION'S CONTROLLER. THE FORMS ARE REVIEWED BY BOTH THE GOVERNING BODY AND THE CONTROLLER. AFTER REVIEW, A TRUSTEE OF THE FUND INDICATES THE APPROVAL OF THE FORM BY COMPLETING FORM 8879 AUTHORIZING THE PAID PREPARER TO ELECTRONICALLY FILE THE FORM 990.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS AN ONGOING SYSTEM OF CONTROLS IN MONITORING TO ENSURE CONFLICTS OF INTEREST DO NOT EXIST WITHIN THE RANKS OF EMPLOYEES AND THOSE INDIVIDUALS CHARGED WITH ORGANIZATIONAL OVERSIGHT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ALL REQUIRED DOCUMENTS AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST TO THOSE WITH A FINANCIAL INTEREST IN THE ORGANIZATION.

THE SALARY AND BENEFITS INFORMATION FOR THE TRUSTEES WHO COULD BE CONSIDERED RELATED TO THE FUND IS REPORTED ON THE RESPECTIVE FORM 990'S FOR THE ENTITIES THAT PAY THE TRUSTEE'S SALARIES AND BENEFITS.
NO CHANGE FROM THE PRIOR YEAR.
